begin_memory_text: We talked about Colorado, because she was wearing a hoodie with the Colorado logo. We talked about our experiences living there.
middle_memory_text: She talked about what it was like having an infant to care for. We talked about our hobbies.
end_memory_text: We talked about moving away from the United States. We also talked about our sleep schedules having been messed up as a result of recent events.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will be okay. I have some difficult things to work through, but I see them resolving in a good way. Specifically, I have conflict with my significant other. It's unclear if we're going to continue to be together or not. I have felt pretty down about it, with the strength of the bad feelings coming and going. I currently feel some degree of hope.
critical_positive: My conversation partner did a good job of moving things along. She asked questions, inquiring about me and getting to know me. I was able to answer these questions and then ask her the same types of things. I felt like she was a good listener. I also did a good job of listening and asking questions.
critical_negative: There were definitely moments where we both went silent because the conversation had fizzled out kind of. I noticed my conversational partner noticing these moments of silence and then thinking of something else to ask me. This makes me think that if I had been more thorough or creative with my questions, we could have kept going more smoothly.

begin_memory_text: Colorado because he saw my sweatshirt and he grew up in Denver and that's where I live now
middle_memory_text: Just random things that came up as we were talking- the pandemic, our families, etc.
end_memory_text: We were talking about his school. I honestly don't remember a lot else at the end until we were saying goodbye. I generally have a terrible memory
rest_of_day_open: Stressful. My boss gave me a big project to finish tomorrow as I was finishing up with work for the day today so I will be really busy tomorrow. I have a 9 month old so I'm always busy with her and don't usually get much sleep. But we're taking my daughter to an event on Sunday so I'm excited for that.
critical_positive: One thing that helped was that we did have some things in common, like location and what he's currently studying and what I used to study. We could relate to each other and it was fairly easy to talk to each other. He was very friendly and we kind of just played off each other's talking to move to different topics.
critical_negative: It was just kind of an awkward situation we were in, being two people who don't know each other but were forced to talk to each other for quite a long time. It's not like making small talk in public because we knew we had to keep talking the whole time. Not knowing anything about each other at all made me nervous to talk about anything that might be an issue, like politics or religion (even though we kind of mentioned those things in the end)
